==English==
===Noun===
'''assembly language'''

# (''Computing'', ''countable'') a low-level [[programming language]] used mostly in writing [[operating system]]s, [[hardware]] [[drivers]], and [[video game]]s. Assembly language allows direct control of hardware devices.

===Typical assembly language instructions===
*MOV AH,2Eh
*INT 21
*CMP BL,CH
*JNE LABEL

